o four year colleges. The student body is primarily black and hispanic and it is common for white kids to be harrassed and bullied based on their skin color. It's the kind of district that you see on you tube where there's a brawl at kindergarten graduationI don't have a lot of money, I rent my apartment and my husband and I both drive 7 year old cars. We make less than $60K a year combined. But we can and will do whatever we need to do to make sure that our son is safe when he starts Kindergarten in the Fall. The school we've chosen is diverse and quiet and they have a strong family friendly vibe. I wish that the public schools were better, I really do. But unless entire sections of town decide to move elsewhere, I won't expose my child to those influences. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1076" language="en" documentId="4340" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Xina the Awesome" date="Aug 29, 2013 5:21PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="29" thumbsDown="0" origId="4340" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1076"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>